// bracket abstraction (see /learn)

// no lambda terms here — binders compile away into combinators, so a lambda is just a way to write a tree

// recursion!

// fix f x = f (fix f) x — each application thaws one unfolding; f gets itself as `self`

// a type is just a predicate

// recursive types are just recursive predicates: zero = t, succ n = t t n

// function types: evaluate the term under all possible inputs? maybe:
//
//   Arrow := {A, B} -> {f} -> {
//       for input in enumerate_trees() {
//           if (A input) and (not (B (f input))) { return false; }
//       }
//       return true;
